# WeChat MP (mp-weixin) rules

WeChat **dependency analysis** drops JS modules that are only referenced from a single page chunk. Runtime then throws `module '…' is not defined` or DevTools throws ENOENT for missing files.

## Do

- Keep **page-only logic inside the `.vue` file** (inline in `<script setup>`), or call APIs via **`@/utils/request`** which every page already loads.
- Put shared HTTP helpers (`fetchRegionDefs`, `emptyPropertyForm`, media helpers) in **`src/utils/request.ts`**.
- Run **`npm run build:mp-weixin`** after changes; open **`dist/build/mp-weixin`** in DevTools (not `src/`).
- Rely on **`scripts/mp-weixin-compat-shims.cjs`** after build — it writes stubs; **never delete** `propertyFormUi.js`, `usePropertyFormUi.js`, or `api/meta.js` from dist.

## Do not

- Add `pages/**/foo.ts` or `composables/useX.ts` used by only one page.
- Add standalone `.vue` media/components on property pages (inline UI instead).
- `import from '@/api/meta'` in pages — use `fetchRegionDefs` / `fetchCodeMasterLabels` from `@/utils/request`.
- Remove post-build stub files from `dist/build/mp-weixin`.

## Build

```bash
npm run build:mp-weixin
```

Then: close DevTools → re-import dist → **清除全部缓存** → compile.
